            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">How long does a bathtub chip repair take?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">Most individual chip repairs take 2-4 hours depending on the size and depth of the damage. Multiple chips in the same bath can usually be repaired in a single visit. The repair needs 24 hours to fully cure before you can use the bath again.</p></div></div>

            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">Can you match the colour of my bathtub?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">Yes. We use professional colour-matching techniques to blend the repair into your existing bath surface. We carry a wide range of standard bath colours and can custom-mix for unusual shades. On a well-done repair, the colour match is virtually seamless.</p></div></div>

            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">Will I be able to see the repair afterwards?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">A professional chip repair is designed to be as invisible as possible. Small surface chips can be repaired to the point where you'd struggle to find the spot. Deeper chips or larger damaged areas may show a very slight texture difference up close, but from normal viewing distance the repair blends in well.</p></div></div>

            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">Is the chip repair waterproof?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">Absolutely. The professional two-part filler and colour-matched coating we apply are fully waterproof once cured. The whole point of the repair is to seal the exposed substrate and prevent water from getting underneath the bath surface.</p></div></div>

            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">How long before I can use the bath after repair?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">We recommend waiting 24 hours before filling the bath with water. This allows the filler and coating to fully cure and harden for maximum durability. Light contact with the repaired area is fine after a few hours.</p></div></div>

            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">What if my bath has multiple chips?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">We can repair multiple chips in a single visit. If your bath has numerous chips, widespread staining, or the surface is generally worn, a <a href="<?php echo esc_url( home_url( '/services/bath-resurfacing-sydney/' ) ); ?>" class="text-primary underline font-medium">full bath resurfacing</a> may be more cost-effective than repairing each chip individually. We'll advise you honestly on which option makes more sense for your situation.</p></div></div>

            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">Can you fix both acrylic and enamel bathtubs?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">Yes. We repair chips on all bath types including enamel-coated steel baths, enamel-coated cast iron baths, and acrylic baths. Each material requires a different approach and filler type, and we carry the right products for all of them.</p></div></div>

            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">How do I get a quote for my chipped bath?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">Send us 2-3 photos of the chip through our <a href="<?php echo esc_url( home_url( '/contact/' ) ); ?>" class="text-primary underline font-medium">contact page</a> and we'll have a quote back to you within hours. Close-up shots showing the size and depth of the damage help us quote accurately. No call-out fee, no obligation. You can also call us directly on <a href="tel:<?php echo timeless_phone_link(); ?>" class="text-primary underline font-medium"><?php echo timeless_phone(); ?></a>.</p></div></div>
        </div>
